node.text:
That’s a wrap on the 2020/21 season and 174 days of operations! While many things looked different this winter, we are incredibly grateful to have been open for nearly 6 months of skiing and riding—especially given the uncertainty we faced at the start of the season. We truly appreciate the resiliency of our employees, skiers & riders, and the Tahoe community as you adapted with us to make it all possible. THANK YOU.
 
We can’t wait to welcome you all back next season for another winter of skiing & riding, and with a new name for these mountains we call home.

🎥: @whiteroomfilms

node.text: With tremendous love for both snow and water, @chuckpatterson takes full advantage of his California roots. Growing up skiing the steeps of Squaw Valley led to his love of surfing. Now his passion for waves compliments how Chuck charges the mountains. Since this video was filmed (pre-Covid) Chuck has even brought both sports together by "wave skiing" the infamous Mavericks surf spot. Shot by @whiteroomfilms & @ben_arnst #skicalifornia

node.title: Untracked  Sea & Snow with Chuck Patterson

node.text: Here’s to a community borne from mountains. Because, while seasons change, the mountains always endure. From big city or small, snowy town – we’re all skiers and riders. And, when we stand together, we’re as tall as the mountains. #WeAreTheMTNS. 💙⛰️💛 With gratitude for this amazing community, @IkonPass doubled renewal discounts for 20/21, and extended all savings until May 27. Together, we will endure.

node.text:
Join Darrel Cruz, Director of the Tribal Historic Preservation Office and Cultural Resources Office of the Washoe Tribe, at High Camp on July 12 and August 9 for a Washoe Cultural Tour. Darrel will share stories of natural landmarks, local plants and animals, Washoe history and culture, and the origins of the name of the Valley. This guided talk is a chance to immerse yourself in the history of the valley & surrounding mountains and view artifacts that show the Washoe way of life that Tribe members seek to preserve today.
 
This event is free, but does not include Aerial Tram access. Bring your 2021/22 Ikon Pass or purchase a special $19 Tram ticket when you register. Ticket sales collected from the event will be donated to the Washoe Cultural Fund. Space is limited, so advanced registration is highly encouraged! Click the link in our bio to reserve your spot.
